03/05/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia on marked the first anniversary of the signing of the Adriatic Charter on Sunday (2 May). The countries' foreign ministers released a joint statement saying the three partners want to accelerate and complete all reforms necessary to meet NATO standards and launch membership talks as soon as possible. The Charter's main objective is to co-ordinate respective integration efforts.
In other news, Croatia's Parliament ratified the Free Trade Agreement with Serbia-Montenegro on Friday. The gradual liberalisation of the trade regime is to be completed by 2007. (HINA, ATA - 02/05/04; HINA - 30/04/04)
